50|$|Sonja Eisenberg has {{designed}} numerous posters and magazine covers. Her work been exhibited widely across the United States and in France, Israel, Japan, <b>Amsterdam,</b> <b>Austria,</b> England, Switzerland and her native Germany. Eisenberg became the WFUNA Cachet designer for the United Nations in 1977 and returned in 1981 {{to design the}} United Nations International Year of the Disabled persons cover for “Discovering Fire for the Second Time.” From 1991 to 1997, she designed the cover of three monthly magazines: “Ziekenhuis & Instelling,” in Amsterdam, Netherlands.|$|R
